      },
      "date": "2012-01-20 23:21:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nGood catch Johann.\n\nDi, it makes sense to check if there are other changes to be made to the LMV code that would avoid compatibility issues in the future.  It looks like the lmv_stripe_md already has an mea_pool_name field.  Johann, would it make sense to split this into an mea_dtpool_name and mea_mdpool_name?  Is there something else we could do to simplify our lives in the future?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bc5f00a2b0b8dd3eb37816647d4cd180f7da4cd2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-20 23:49:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJohann, thanks for bringing this up. I actually made another patch for cleanup lmv for DNE patch. There is a field called layout_version which might be for this purpose. If I remember it correctly. \n\n http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1965 \n\nAndreas, could you please review that. or maybe just lustre_idl.h  to see the definition of lmv_mds_md in case I miss some fields.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
